
|WKBSYNTAX
======
|YKBwho <argument|#>

|WKBDESCRIPTION
===========
|YKBwho         |YKO- shows everyone on at that time.
|YKBwho -text   |YKO- uses the compact text list instead of the Darkflow window.
|YKBwho play    |YKO- shows all players on at that time.
|YKBwho wiz     |YKO- shows all Wizards on at that time.
|YKBwho level <#> |YKO- shows all players over that given level on at that time.
|YKBwho ghost   |YKO- shows all ghosts on at that time.
|YKBwho new     |YKO- shows all the newbies on at that time.
|YKBwho legend  |YKO- shows all the Legends on at that time.
|YKBwho hero    |YKO- shows all heroes on at that time.
|YKBwho pk      |YKO- shows all registered player killers on at that time.
|YKBwho male    |YKO- shows all the males on at that time.
|YKBwho female  |YKO- shows all the females on at that time.
|YKBwho neuter  |YKO- shows all the neuters on at that time.
|YKBwho single  |YKO- shows all unmarried players on at that time.
|YKBwho pavail  |YKO- shows all players available for a party at that time.
|YKBwho <race>  |YKO- shows all members of <race> on at that time.
|YKBwho <guild> |YKO- shows all the <guild> members on at that time.
|YKBwho mitra   |YKO- shows all the devotees of Mitra on at that time.
|YKBwho gaea    |YKO- shows all the devotees of Gaea on at that time.
|YKBwho web     |YKO- shows the name and address of all players on who
              have set their web page address.

# is an optional argument to pause the listing length. Default is 15.
Invisible players will show as "hidden", though this does not
apply to the user running the command.
